value.title: Trump Names Danly to Head FERC, Replacing Chatterjee
value.excerpt: Neil Chatterjee, who has backed policies in support of clean energy, is being replaced as head of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission by fellow commissioner James Danly.

value.title: Donald Trump's aides are increasingly gloomy – and mad at other GOP officials
value.excerpt: Some aides to President Donald Trump said they're not giving up on the election, but they're also bracing for the worst. They're also upset with other Republicans who have not spoken out against the ongoing election count as forcefully as Trump has.

value.title: Michigan secretary of state calls Trump lawsuit 'frivolous'

value.title: Pennsylvania's Democratic governor calls Trump remarks 'partisan attack'
value.excerpt: Pennsylvania's Democratic Governor Tom Wolf on Wednesday called President Donald Trump's unsubstantiated claim about fraud in the U.S. presidential election a "partisan attack", and said his state was working hard to count more than 1 million mail-in ballots.

value.title: Ex-ESPN host Jemele Hill says 'it's on White people' if Trump wins reelection: 'No one else'

value.title: Barbara Res helped build Trump Tower. She says she saw Donald Trump ignore experts and disrespect employees in her 18 years working with him.
value.excerpt: Donald Trump has long displayed certain behaviors, says Barbara Res, whose new book "Tower of Lies" recounts almost 2 decades of working with him.

value.title: CNN's Don Lemon hits network for airing Trump's 'propaganda' visit to RNC office
value.excerpt: CNN anchor Don Lemon questioned the judgment of his own network Tuesday after it broadcast remarks President Trump made during his visit to a Republican National Committee office.

value.title: The Trump campaign has set up two ‘war rooms’ in the White House complex
value.excerpt: President Trump’s campaign has set up two election night “war rooms” in the White House complex, raising questions anew about the intermingling of the governmental and the political in the Trump administration.

value.title: In St. Petersburg, Fla., Trump's Character Is in Focus
value.excerpt: With millions of Floridians having already voted, the Election Day line quickly diminished outside the largest polling location in St. Petersburg, Fla. The city resides in Pinellas County, one of the bellwether counties in the country's largest battleground state.

value.title: Trump May Try to Fire Wray, but FBI Director Has GOP Support on Capitol Hill
value.excerpt: President Trump has frequently and openly speculated about firing FBI Director Christopher Wray after the election, but Mr. Wray continues to enjoy support from some GOP senators..

value.title: 'Winning is easy. Losing is never easy': Trump stops by RNC office in Virginia

value.title: Trump's campaign booked out YouTube's homepage for Election Day. YouTube won't let that happen again — but insists it's nothing to do with Trump.
value.excerpt: YouTube will no longer allow advertisers to book out its main homepage slots for days at a time. The change had nothing to do with Trump, Google said.

value.title: Exclusive: Tired of Trump, Deutsche Bank wants out but sees no good options - sources
value.excerpt: Deutsche Bank AG is looking for ways to end its relationship with President Donald Trump after the U.S. elections, as it tires of the negative publicity stemming from the ties, according to three senior bank officials with direct knowledge of the matter.
